reviews.review_text: 81 Greek - Another amazing recording! There was a poster made years ago that shows the band blissing out with Garcia's head cranked sideways as he belts out lyrics. The crowds arms are up above their shoulders as they clap in approval. There are red roses on the stage and the famous Greek tie dyes done by Courtney in the background. I think it was actually from Greek '83 but to me it represents how the crowd must have been feeling at the end of the beautiful MORNING DEW from this show. Get it.

Best of the AUD sources While I tend to gravitate towards Walker and Wise AUDs, those sources are unfortunately marred by clapping too close to the mics. This is a phenomenal show and while I wish the sound was a little crisper, it's a minor quibble. Always loved the He's Gone>Truckin' combo and this is a particularly tasty treat here.
